data.title: Duluth
data.meta_description: The birthplace of Bob Dylan and a shipping hub where repurposed industrial buildings now house vibrant food and drink spots, Duluth buzzes with year-round excitement on the shore of Lake Superior. Discover dramatic natural beauty, thriving arts and culture, restaurants, breweries, lakefront trails and more in northeast Minnesota's biggest city.
data.text:
Top Things To Do

From watching a tall ship sail into the world’s furthest inland harbor to exhilarating outdoor adventures in every season, Duluth is home to an incredible array of things to do.

Read More

5 Ways to Do Duluth

Whether you’re all about the outdoors, traveling with your kids, looking to explore the city by the sip or experience arts and history, there’s a Duluth adventure that’s just your style.

Read More

Go Mountain Biking

A premier destination for mountain bikers, Duluth teems with trailheads that beckon riders to explore the varied terrain on two wheels. From Lester Park to Spirit Mountain, Duluth has trails to suit riders of every skill level.

Read More

Hop on the Beer Trail

The journey along Minnesota’s storied North Shore Beer Trail starts and ends with samplings at Duluth’s award-winning craft breweries and ale houses. See what’s on tap in this three-day exploration of IPAs, lagers and more.

Read More

North Shore Bliss

Between Duluth and the Canadian border lies a veritable paradise for lovers of natural beauty. When you set out from Duluth, experience majestic sights like Lake Superior sparkling amid jagged cliffs and stands of pine.

Read More
